<strong>HELP for Victims of the California – SoCal Fires…</strong>

<strong>Everyone is posting a ton of news, pics and media of the devastation. HELP, in some form is my contribution. If you are directly involved or have family who haven’t heard from! Review the following list for many ways to get help! NOTICE- I'M NOT MAKING MONEY AND NO CLICK BATE - NO ADS HERE- THIS IS PURE, HELP, A PLACE TO GET HELP DURING THE DISASTER OR YOU HELP-DONATE TO THESE COMPANIES! SHARE THIS POST/WEBSITE OUT!</strong>

[caption id="attachment_210" align="aligncenter" width="1080"]<img class="size-full wp-image-210" src="https://bridgenewz.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/LA2025-fire.webp" alt="LA2025-fire" width="1080" height="632" /> LA2025-fire as taken 01-09-2025 ryanbridglal[/caption]

1<sup>st</sup>, post and mark you are safe everyday on Social Media – FACEBOOK CRISIS RESPONSE - until you have relocated to a place with constant signal, power, utilities and communication. All of your family &amp; friends who follow you, will see it and know. OK, they are alive and safe; we will hear from them after they have proper refuge.

&nbsp;

[caption id="attachment_202" align="aligncenter" width="1005"]<img class="size-full wp-image-202" src="https://bridgenewz.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/facebookCrisisResponse.webp" alt="facebookCrisisResponse" width="1005" height="358" /> facebookCrisisResponse - as referenced, 01/09/2025[/caption]

<span style="font-size: large;"><b>*** FACEBOOK - Mark yourself safe or check on someone else on Facebook</b></span>

When you receive a notification from Facebook asking if you're safe, click <b>I'm Safe</b>.
<ol>
 	<li>Go to <a href="https://www.facebook.com/crisisresponse/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Crisis Response</a> and select a Crisis page.</li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/crisisresponse/">https://www.facebook.com/crisisresponse/</a></li>
 	<li>On the Crisis page, click <b>Safety Check</b>.</li>
 	<li>Below <b>Friends in the area</b>, you'll see a list of your friends who are <b>Marked Safe </b>and a list of your friends who are <b>Not Marked Safe Yet</b>. Use the search bar to search for a friend using their name, but keep in mind that you can only ask people you're friends with on Facebook if they're safe.</li>
 	<li>Click <b>Ask If Safe</b> next to the person's name.</li>
</ol>
Once you ask if a friend is safe, they'll receive a notification and be able to mark themselves safe.

<a href="https://www.facebook.com/help/516656825135759/">https://www.facebook.com/help/516656825135759/</a>

