<span style="font-size: large;"><b>*** AMERICAN RED CROSS – INSTANT RELIEF</b></span>
<h5 class="western"><b>Need Help Now?</b></h5>
If you are in immediate need of help, please <a href="https://www.redcross.org/find-your-local-chapter.html" target="Target"><b>contact your local Red Cross »</b></a> or <a href="https://www.redcross.org/get-help/disaster-relief-and-recovery-services/find-an-open-shelter.html" target="Target"><b>find an open shelter » </b></a>

<a href="https://www.redcross.org/find-your-local-chapter.html">https://www.redcross.org/find-your-local-chapter.html</a>

<a href="https://www.redcross.org/get-help/disaster-relief-and-recovery-services/find-an-open-shelter.html">https://www.redcross.org/get-help/disaster-relief-and-recovery-services/find-an-open-shelter.html</a>

INSTANT SHELTERS – MEALS/SNACKS – SUPPLIES – HEALTH SERVICES – MENTAL HEALTH SERVICES – EMERGENCY RESPONSE/VOLUNTEERS

“<b>We respond to an emergency every 8 minutes.</b>

No one else does this: not the government, not other charities. From small house fires to multi-state natural disasters, the American Red Cross goes wherever we’re needed, so people can have clean water, safe shelter and hot meals when they need them most.
<ul>
 	<li>We respond to an average of about <b>65,000</b> disasters every year</li>
 	<li><b>95%</b> of our disaster relief workers are volunteers</li>
 	<li>The vast majority of disasters we respond to are home fires</li>
</ul>
“ <a href="https://www.redcross.org/about-us/our-work/disaster-relief.html">https://www.redcross.org/about-us/our-work/disaster-relief.html</a> 01/09/2025

